.TH "vmw_kms_new_framebuffer" 9 "vmw_kms_new_framebuffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_kms_new_framebuffer \- Create a new framebuffer.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct vmw_framebuffer *" vmw_kms_new_framebuffer
.BI "(struct vmw_private *dev_priv "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_buffer_object *bo "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_surface *surface "  ","
.BI "bool only_2d "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_mode_fb_cmd2 *mode_cmd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev_priv" 12
Pointer to device private struct.
.IP "bo" 12
Pointer to buffer object to wrap the kms framebuffer around.
Either \fIbo\fP or \fIsurface\fP must be NULL.
.IP "surface" 12
Pointer to a surface to wrap the kms framebuffer around.
Either \fIbo\fP or \fIsurface\fP must be NULL.
.IP "only_2d" 12
No presents will occur to this buffer object based framebuffer.
This helps the code to do some important optimizations.
.IP "mode_cmd" 12
Frame-buffer metadata.
